                android:text=" Prepare the Lobster Filling:

In a bowl, combine the chopped lobster meat, ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic, lemon zest, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined. Adjust seasoning to taste.
2. Make the Pasta Dough (if making from scratch):

On a clean surface, make a mound with the flour and create a well in the center.

Crack the eggs into the well and add a pinch of salt.

Using a fork, gradually incorporate the flour into the eggs until a dough forms.

Knead the dough for about 10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic.

Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let it rest for at least 30 minutes.

3. Roll Out the Pasta Dough:

Divide the pasta dough into small portions and roll each portion into thin sheets using a pasta machine or a rolling pin.

Place spoonfuls of the lobster filling onto one sheet of pasta, leaving space between each mound.

Place another sheet of pasta on top and press around each mound to seal the ravioli.

Cut the ravioli into individual pieces using a knife or a ravioli cutter.

4. Cook the Lobster Ravioli:

Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.

Carefully add the lobster ravioli to the boiling water and cook until they float to the surface, usually 3-4 minutes.

Remove the ravioli with a slotted spoon and set aside.

5. Prepare the Sauce:

In a skillet, melt the butter over medium heat.

Add minced garlic and sautÃ© until fragrant.

Pour in the white wine and let it simmer for a couple of minutes.

Stir in the heavy cream, salt, and black pepper. Cook until the sauce thickens slightly.

6. Serve:

Plate the lobster ravioli and drizzle the creamy garlic butter sauce over them.

Garnish with fresh parsley.

Serve immediately and enjoy your delicious Lobster Ravioli!"
